  <title>How to view Installed applications from Containers?</title>

  <p><gui>Vanilla OS Control Center</gui> allows you to view the GUI applications installed inside multiple <gui>apx</gui> containers in a unified place.</p>
  
  <p>Applications with a desktop entry are listed in the <gui>Installed Applications</gui> menu.</p>
 
         <figure>
                <title><gui>Sub System</gui> panel in Vanilla OS Control Center listing <gui>Installed Applications</gui></title>
                <media type="image" its:translate="no" src="media/vanilla-control-center-subsystem-enter.png"/>
         </figure>
 
 <p> You can execute the application by clicking on the <gui>Start</gui> (Play) button beside the required application.</p>
